          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>This time, we learned about proofs in the natural deduction system NJ, as well as two close relative systems NM and NK.</html:p>
            <html:p>Proofs are made up of rules, and you can use whatever rules you like to build a proof, so long as the rules are used correctly.</html:p>
